        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 18 at 2:12PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 212 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ashdown, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ashdown, Wilton, Ogden, Richmond, Pine Prairie and Millwood.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
